Launch: honest trafficPlatforms handling + payload logging

Empirical finding: NewsBreak's public /ad-set/create endpoint accepts
trafficPlatforms without error (HTTP 200) but silently drops the
field — the ad set comes out with Unlimited inventory. This means
the previous best-effort retry, which only triggered on HTTP 4xx,
never fired, so users got no indication that NewsBreak-only was
not applied.

Changes:
- bulk_launcher.py: after a successful create_ad_set, if the user
  asked for NewsBreak-only, make a second-pass call to
  /ad-set/update with just {trafficPlatforms}. Emit a warning in
  the launch result either way (success or failure), since the
  public API does not return this field on read and we can't
  programmatically confirm it was applied.
- bulk_launcher.py: add structured JSON logging of the create/update
  payloads and responses so Render logs are useful for post-launch
  debugging (previously all `app.logger.info` calls were silently
  dropped because Flask runs at WARNING by default).
- app.py: root `logging.basicConfig(level=INFO, stream=stderr)` so
  module loggers (bulk_launcher, rules_engine, etc.) actually emit.
  Overridable via LOG_LEVEL env var.
- templates/launch.html: rewrite the inventory hint to be honest
  about what we observed today — "public API silently ignores this
  field, verify Inventory in Ad Manager after launch".

Made-with: Cursor
